<chapter id="upgrade_manager">
  <title>Upgrades</title>

  <para>
    The Upgrade Manager controls software updates and new features for your &eg;.  The Upgrade Manager is launched from the main Administrative Interface by pushing the <guilabel>Upgrade</guilabel> button as seen in <xref linkend="upgrade_manager_launch_upgrade_manager"/>.
  </para>
  <figure id="upgrade_manager_launch_upgrade_manager">
    <title>Launching the upgrade Manager</title>
    <mediaobject>
      <imageobject>
        <imagedata fileref="figure/upgrademngr/launch_upgrade.png" />
      </imageobject>
    </mediaobject>
  </figure>    
  <para>
    Please visit <xref linkend="upgrade_manager_manual"/> or more details on manually upgrading your &eg;.  To configure your &eg; for automatic upgrades, please refer to <xref linkend="upgrade_manager_automatic"/>.
  </para>

  <sect1 id="upgrade_manager_adminui">
    <title>Administrative Interface</title>
    <para>
      The Administrative Interface is divided into two sections.  The first section, covered in <xref linkend="upgrade_manager_manual"/>, discusses how to manually upgrade your &eg;.  <xref linkend="upgrade_manager_automatic"/> discusses how to automatically schedule upgrades as they are made available.
    </para>

